      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Another very modest maiden where AIRWAVES (1) gets chance. Midfield last couple which is pretty good form for this and best figures stand well above most. Looks his race. VALADORE (10) has been freshened since finishing midfield at Gatton latest and wasn't far away at Kilcoy the start prior. Like AIRWAVES that's good form for this and should be in the finish. HIGH SOBRIETY (7) was beaten just a nose at country level last time and looks a strong chance with a repeat. Drawn well and will be winding up strongly. JOT GIRL (8) was huge odds at debut but bombed the start and was always at the tail. That has proven a hot form race though and with the experience under the belt can improve out of sight. AMELIA'S PRINCE (2) was also slow to begin when resuming and can do better.",
